Wine Variety Clustering and Classification with K-Means and Decision Tree Classifier Models

Applying a K-Means clustering algorithm to unlabeled wine chemical data to gain insight into group patterns in the data and developing a dicision tree classifier model to predict wine groupings.

WCSS = []
for i in range(1,11):
    model = KMeans(n_clusters = i,init = 'k-means++')
    model.fit(df)
    WCSS.append(model.inertia_)
fig = plt.figure(figsize = (8,8))
plt.plot(range(1,11),WCSS, linewidth=4, markersize=12,marker='o',color = 'green')
plt.xticks(np.arange(11))
plt.xlabel("Number of clusters")
plt.ylabel("WCSS")
plt.show()

kmeans = cluster.KMeans(n_clusters=3, init="k-means++")
kmeans = kmeans.fit(df)
df["clusters"] = kmeans.labels_
df.to_csv("w_clusters.csv")
df.head()
